The code calculates the "total" from the nested list "groups", which should
should return 9, however it is incorrectly setting each iteration's total t
to the last entry amount because of how inner loop is structured. It assign
assigns the value of 'entry.amount' only when it iterates through entries f
for the last group in 'group.entries'. To fix this issue, we need to add up
up all amounts during both iterations over groups and entries:

```tundra
val groups = [
  {
    name: "north",
    entries: [
      { amount: 2 },
      { amount: 3 }
     ]
   },
  {
    name: "south",
    entries: [
      { amount: 4 }
     ]
   }
];

var total = 0;
for (group in groups) {
  for (entry in group.entries) {
    total = total + entry.amount;
  }
}

print(total);
```
